message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Server-Client Interaction Benchmarking Across Two Nodes Under Bandwidth
  Shaping and Energy Measurement Conditions
abstract: This dataset contains results from benchmarking experiments measuring transfer
  performance, timing metrics, energy consumption, and network conditions between
  two nodes. The methodology involved running multiple loops with different configurations
  to evaluate various QUIC implementations under controlled bandwidth limits. Evaluation
  scripts were used to calculate goodput, verify consistency via checksums, analyze
  timing data, assess success rates, and generate visualizations like box plots comparing
  performance across file sizes.
